11. Use Container Widget with decoration property in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter uses the decoration property to apply advanced styling such as:

Background color
Border
Border radius (rounded corners)
Box shadow
Gradient

It uses the BoxDecoration class for customization.

⚠️ Note: When using decoration, do not use the color property directly (color should be inside BoxDecoration).

//main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerDecorationExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerDecorationExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container Decoration Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          height: 150,
          width: 250,
          decoration: BoxDecoration(
            color: Colors.blue,
            border: Border.all(color: Colors.black, width: 3),
            borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(15),
            boxShadow: [
              BoxShadow(
                color: Colors.grey,
                blurRadius: 5,
                spreadRadius: 2,
              ),
            ],
          ),
          child: Center(
            child: Text(
              "Decorated Box",
              style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}